main event: On April 4, 1960, several lights were observed briefly in La Camp, Louisiana, leaving no physical traces, and the case was classified as unidentified.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 2-3 seconds., The lights appeared and disappeared without leaving any traces., Paint samples from impact positions were collected but proved negative for any known materials., The investigation noted that apparent rockets were involved, but no physical evidence was found., Witnesses reported unusual characteristics of the observed lights, causing a great deal of interest among local residents.
